1
00:01:33,280 --> 00:01:34,519
All this blocking and cutting...

2
00:01:34,519 --> 00:01:35,079
I'm telling you,

3
00:01:35,079 --> 00:01:36,200
you can't listen to doctors.

4
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:37,959
Exactly.

5
00:01:38,239 --> 00:01:39,079
It's not that

6
00:01:39,079 --> 00:01:40,480
I don't want you treated.

7
00:01:40,480 --> 00:01:41,239
You know that.

8
00:01:42,319 --> 00:01:42,840
Come on.

9
00:01:44,159 --> 00:01:45,560
Think about it this way.

10
00:01:46,439 --> 00:01:47,760
If they put you through all that

11
00:01:48,280 --> 00:01:49,480
and delay things for a year or two,

12
00:01:49,519 --> 00:01:50,040
then by then

13
00:01:50,079 --> 00:01:51,200
you really might not be able to have another child.

14
00:01:51,680 --> 00:01:53,840
Besides, they never said

15
00:01:53,840 --> 00:01:55,840
your condition would definitely kill you.

16
00:01:56,359 --> 00:01:57,040
You're just believing the worst-case scenario.

17
00:01:58,920 --> 00:02:01,120
All that talk about "mouse holes" and cutting things open—

18
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:03,719
they're obviously trying to scare you.

19
00:02:04,799 --> 00:02:06,319
We've already had two kids.

20
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:07,280
How could the third one

21
00:02:07,319 --> 00:02:08,039
suddenly put your life at risk?

22
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:09,439
That makes no sense.

23
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:11,199
They just want your money.

24
00:02:11,599 --> 00:02:12,400
That's why they want surgery.

25
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:14,879
But after hearing them,

26
00:02:15,639 --> 00:02:17,479
I really am a little scared.

27
00:02:17,639 --> 00:02:18,879
Oh, now you're scared?

28
00:02:19,080 --> 00:02:19,879
You're usually so careless,

29
00:02:19,879 --> 00:02:20,879
and braver than I am.

30
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:25,280
You don't actually want another baby, do you?

31
00:02:25,319 --> 00:02:26,759
Is that why you're making excuses?

32
00:02:27,439 --> 00:02:29,280
Listen, Zhang Diao'e.

33
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:30,400
If we never have a son,

34
00:02:30,719 --> 00:02:31,800
we'll end up like your parents,

35
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:33,879
bullied and called a family with no heir.

36
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:35,680
Don't regret it then.

37
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:39,120
I never said I didn't want one.

38
00:02:39,479 --> 00:02:40,159
Every day,

39
00:02:40,159 --> 00:02:41,719
I work myself to death earning money.

40
00:02:42,159 --> 00:02:43,520
I pay for your food and living expenses.

41
00:02:43,759 --> 00:02:44,680
I even pay for your treatment.

42
00:02:44,759 --> 00:02:45,919
I, Lü Zhaobang, haven't done anything

43
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:46,919
to wrong you, have I?

44
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:48,520
You can't be this heartless.

45
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:49,800
Do you want my bloodline to end too?

46
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:51,800
Enough. Stop talking.

47
00:02:52,759 --> 00:02:53,560
Fine. We'll have one.

48
00:02:53,919 --> 00:02:54,759
I won't get the surgery.

49
00:03:02,439 --> 00:03:03,840
All right, then.

50
00:03:06,159 --> 00:03:06,919
You should lie down for a while.

51
00:03:07,199 --> 00:03:07,680
The construction site

52
00:03:08,039 --> 00:03:09,199
keeps calling me.

53
00:03:09,759 --> 00:03:10,400
I have to go.

54
00:03:10,639 --> 00:03:11,439
If anything happens,

55
00:03:11,479 --> 00:03:12,319
call me anytime.

56
00:03:12,439 --> 00:03:12,759
You hear me?

57
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:13,280
Okay.

58
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:15,120
Drink some water.

59
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:16,759
I'm going.

60
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:35,039
Zhang Diao'e's pulmonary arteriovenous malformation

61
00:03:35,159 --> 00:03:36,479
is really quite rare.

62
00:03:36,719 --> 00:03:37,719
I've never seen

63
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:38,680
a real case before.

64
00:03:40,159 --> 00:03:40,719
I have.

65
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:42,520
Back when I was at Xili Hospital,

66
00:03:42,599 --> 00:03:43,240
I worked with Professor Cao

67
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:44,280
and Thoracic Surgery on one.

68
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:46,080
In the past,

69
00:03:46,080 --> 00:03:46,919
these were all treated surgically.

70
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:51,400
But I still want to consider

71
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:52,280
transcatheter embolization first.

72
00:03:53,639 --> 00:03:54,840
It's much less invasive.

73
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:56,360
Why?

74
00:03:57,360 --> 00:03:59,039
In Zhang Diao'e's case,

75
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:01,520
She has multiple pulmonary arteriovenous malformations,

76
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:03,280
but confined to the left lower lobe.

77
00:04:03,599 --> 00:04:04,599
A thoracoscopic procedure

78
00:04:04,599 --> 00:04:05,360
would be straightforward.

79
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:08,000
And right now, you don't have

80
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:09,520
an occluder specifically designed

81
00:04:09,560 --> 00:04:10,319
for pulmonary vascular lesions.

82
00:04:17,639 --> 00:04:18,680
Whatever you do,

83
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:20,120
don't use an off-label device.

84
00:04:21,040 --> 00:04:21,759
I won't.

85
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:23,920
But you're right.

86
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:24,639
I need to look into

87
00:04:24,680 --> 00:04:25,720
the newest products.

88
00:04:26,079 --> 00:04:27,199
It is a rare case, after all.

89
00:04:27,519 --> 00:04:28,279
How about this?

90
00:04:28,439 --> 00:04:29,319
I'll ask a specialist

91
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:30,120
from Thoracic Surgery.

92
00:04:30,199 --> 00:04:31,399
We can call a consult if necessary.

93
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:33,560
But you said

94
00:04:33,639 --> 00:04:35,360
this patient is in a hurry to get pregnant.

95
00:04:36,279 --> 00:04:37,800
Does that mean she doesn't want treatment?

96
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:40,639
Why does Zhang Diao'e

97
00:04:40,639 --> 00:04:42,279
want another baby right now?

98
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:45,920
Why don't you try persuading her again?

99
00:04:46,759 --> 00:04:47,639
You go.

100
00:04:48,079 --> 00:04:48,720
I already did.

101
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:49,879
She wouldn't listen to me.

102
00:04:51,240 --> 00:04:52,079
Do you think it's because

103
00:04:52,079 --> 00:04:52,959
I'm a man?

104
00:04:54,759 --> 00:04:55,560
I get the feeling

105
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:56,879
she listens to you.

106
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:00,920
Director Zhou and Director Lin

107
00:05:00,920 --> 00:05:01,720
have already told her everything.

108
00:05:02,759 --> 00:05:03,519
No matter what we say,

109
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:04,839
we're only doctors.

110
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:06,240
We're not anyone's parents.

111
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:09,839
You can't put it like that.

112
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:11,439
People say doctors should care like parents.

113
00:05:12,959 --> 00:05:14,199
You can't be so cold.

114
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:22,000
I'm not obligated to warm anyone's heart.

115
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:32,639
What era are we living in?

116
00:05:32,720 --> 00:05:34,000
Risking your life just to have a son?

117
00:05:34,279 --> 00:05:35,360
Did you come from the Qing dynasty?

118
00:05:36,319 --> 00:05:37,839
Did no one tell you New China was founded?

119
00:05:38,439 --> 00:05:39,319
Did nine years of compulsory education

120
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:40,639
go straight into a dog's stomach?

121
00:05:42,199 --> 00:05:43,800
That's no way to talk to me.

122
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:45,160
The sun's in my eyes. Pull the shade.

123
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:46,759
What do you know?

124
00:05:47,639 --> 00:05:48,600
In the countryside,

125
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:50,279
you have to have a son.

126
00:05:51,279 --> 00:05:51,959
Take me, for example.

127
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:53,639
My household registration is still with my parents,

128
00:05:53,639 --> 00:05:54,639
but I don't get any land.

129
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:56,360
That's against the rules.

130
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:58,600
If I hadn't left

131
00:05:58,600 --> 00:05:59,240
all these years ago,

132
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:00,279
I'd still be kept in the dark.

133
00:06:00,759 --> 00:06:02,240
And even if you have a son

134
00:06:02,399 --> 00:06:03,360
and he gets land,

135
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:04,040
your two daughters

136
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:05,079
still won't get any, right?

137
00:06:05,399 --> 00:06:07,199
At least there'd be a man in the family.

138
00:06:07,279 --> 00:06:08,000
If anything happens later,

139
00:06:08,079 --> 00:06:09,360
someone can stand up for us.

140
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:10,079
What if

141
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:11,079
you have another daughter?

142
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:12,480
Impossible.

143
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:13,319
Third time's the charm.

144
00:06:13,399 --> 00:06:14,480
I've already had two daughters.

145
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:15,600
I can't possibly have another.

146
00:06:15,879 --> 00:06:17,319
A fortune-teller already said

147
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:19,680
Zhaobang is destined to have a son,

148
00:06:19,839 --> 00:06:21,480
and Tingting and Panpan are destined to have a younger brother.

149
00:06:22,319 --> 00:06:23,800
There's another possibility.

150
00:06:24,079 --> 00:06:24,800
What possibility?

151
00:06:25,319 --> 00:06:26,000
You refuse treatment,

152
00:06:26,519 --> 00:06:28,120
work yourself into an early grave,

153
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:29,839
and your husband has a son

154
00:06:29,839 --> 00:06:30,560
with another woman.

155
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:31,800
Then Tingting and Panpan

156
00:06:31,839 --> 00:06:32,639
will still have a younger brother.

157
00:06:32,720 --> 00:06:34,480
Can't you wish me well for once?

158
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:37,120
Not everyone is like you,

159
00:06:37,399 --> 00:06:39,000
in your thirties and still unmarried,

160
00:06:39,199 --> 00:06:40,319
with no kids.

161
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:41,639
At every age,

162
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:43,040
there are things you're supposed to do.

163
00:06:43,439 --> 00:06:44,240
So once you reach

164
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:45,439
the national average life expectancy,

165
00:06:45,519 --> 00:06:46,680
should you just drop dead?

166
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:49,680
I never realized

167
00:06:49,759 --> 00:06:51,040
you had such a sharp tongue.

168
00:06:52,959 --> 00:06:54,639
Can you not have children?

169
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:55,399
No.

170
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:56,720
If you really have that problem,

171
00:06:56,839 --> 00:06:57,319
I'm telling you,

172
00:06:57,519 --> 00:06:58,279
there was a woman in our village

173
00:06:58,399 --> 00:06:59,879
just like you.

174
00:07:00,759 --> 00:07:02,000
She saw an old Chinese medicine doctor,

175
00:07:02,079 --> 00:07:04,040
and last year she popped out a big, healthy boy.

176
00:07:04,319 --> 00:07:05,560
What's wrong with you?

177
00:07:06,079 --> 00:07:07,279
You think everyone is like you,

178
00:07:07,399 --> 00:07:08,399
obsessed with this all day,

179
00:07:08,519 --> 00:07:09,199
treating yourself like

180
00:07:09,279 --> 00:07:10,560
a walking baby-making machine?

181
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:11,920
You're practically kissing me.

182
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:13,560
I'm only trying to help.

183
00:07:13,959 --> 00:07:15,399
Who wants your help?

184
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:17,399
Have you ever been pregnant?

185
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:21,199
Who?

186
00:07:22,439 --> 00:07:22,839
Hello?

187
00:07:24,560 --> 00:07:25,079
You're here?

188
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:26,959
The ward is on the sixth floor.

189
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:30,639
Okay.

190
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:31,759
Wait there.

191
00:07:31,839 --> 00:07:32,360
I'll come find you.

192
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:34,000
Bye.

193
00:07:34,879 --> 00:07:35,720
A man, huh?

194
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:37,160
So gentle.

195
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:38,600
Hey.

196
00:07:40,439 --> 00:07:42,079
Look how happy you are.

197
00:07:42,639 --> 00:07:44,160
Maybe you should have him checked.

198
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:45,680
Shut up.

199
00:07:46,079 --> 00:07:47,240
Try wishing me well.

200
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:16,720
I didn't expect hospitals

201
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:17,720
to have cafés now.

202
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:22,920
Sorry.

203
00:08:23,279 --> 00:08:24,439
No photos, please. Thank you.

204
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:25,160
Okay.

205
00:08:27,639 --> 00:08:27,920
Over here.

206
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:28,639
Come this way.

207
00:08:29,279 --> 00:08:30,720
My left side looks better. You forgot?

208
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:31,879
I forgot.

209
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:33,799
All right.

210
00:08:34,440 --> 00:08:34,799
Got it.

211
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:35,679
Let me see.

212
00:08:36,519 --> 00:08:37,120
I'll send it to Mia.

213
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:38,320
She can retouch it for you.

214
00:08:39,759 --> 00:08:40,600
Send it to me.

215
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:41,240
I'll edit it myself.

216
00:08:42,559 --> 00:08:44,039
a fragile-beauty look

217
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:45,200
performed really well.

218
00:08:46,039 --> 00:08:46,600
I know.

219
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:53,279
Have you gained weight?

220
00:08:54,559 --> 00:08:55,000
Have I?

221
00:08:57,399 --> 00:08:58,080
You have.

222
00:09:00,519 --> 00:09:01,399
Maybe.

223
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:02,440
Probably because lately

224
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,639
I haven't exercised much in the hospital.

225
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:06,039
You said it yourself:

226
00:09:06,799 --> 00:09:07,759
a little weight ruins everything.

227
00:09:09,240 --> 00:09:09,759
I know.

228
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:11,799
This is your zodiac year.

229
00:09:12,080 --> 00:09:13,159
If you keep looking like this,

230
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:15,000
you'll only be able to sell plus-size clothes.

231
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:16,080
All right, I get it.

232
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:16,799
Stop nagging.

233
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:19,679
If there's nothing else,

234
00:09:19,679 --> 00:09:20,720
don't keep staying here.

235
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:22,279
Hospitals are bad luck.

236
00:09:27,919 --> 00:09:29,159
You haven't been home these past few days.

237
00:09:30,440 --> 00:09:31,840
I went to Shenzhen on business.

238
00:09:32,759 --> 00:09:34,320
Then you need to check on Xiaobai.

239
00:09:34,320 --> 00:09:35,480
She gets lonely.

240
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:36,919
She's fine.

241
00:09:37,559 --> 00:09:38,919
Cats are resilient.

242
00:09:42,399 --> 00:09:43,720
Order 83, thank you.

243
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:44,559
Brother Xu,

244
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:45,799
I need to talk to you about something.

245
00:09:45,919 --> 00:09:47,240
It's not ready yet. Please wait.

246
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:47,720
Okay.

247
00:09:47,919 --> 00:09:49,559
My mom's place in the suburbs

248
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:50,799
has been leaking for ages,

249
00:09:51,039 --> 00:09:52,000
so it's being renovated.

250
00:09:52,799 --> 00:09:54,799
And with me in the hospital

251
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:56,399
doing all these tests,

252
00:09:56,519 --> 00:09:57,440
I've spent quite a lot.

253
00:09:59,399 --> 00:10:00,639
The doctor says

254
00:10:00,759 --> 00:10:01,960
the next stage will cost even more.

255
00:10:02,559 --> 00:10:03,399
Could you transfer

256
00:10:03,399 --> 00:10:04,360
some of my money back to me first?

257
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,480
It's all tied up in operations.

258
00:10:06,879 --> 00:10:08,039
The company is

259
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:09,399
at a critical stage of growth.

260
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:10,840
I don't dare touch that money.

261
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:14,720
I haven't touched it at all.

262
00:10:15,639 --> 00:10:16,879
It's been two years.

263
00:10:16,879 --> 00:10:18,440
There can't be zero profit.

264
00:10:18,639 --> 00:10:19,600
Just transfer me

265
00:10:19,639 --> 00:10:20,679
some of my share.

266
00:10:20,679 --> 00:10:21,840
Don't rush.

267
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:23,200
Once you're discharged,

268
00:10:23,559 --> 00:10:25,039
I'll reconnect you with work.

269
00:10:25,879 --> 00:10:27,120
Then the money will start coming in.

270
00:10:32,559 --> 00:10:34,480
I wouldn't be asking

271
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:35,279
if I weren't really broke

272
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:36,639
and desperate.

273
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:37,679
I know. I know.

274
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:38,399
But

275
00:10:38,879 --> 00:10:40,480
we agreed before.

276
00:10:42,559 --> 00:10:44,879
It was an investment in our love.

277
00:10:45,519 --> 00:10:46,559
We were going to build

278
00:10:46,559 --> 00:10:47,679
a business empire

279
00:10:47,679 --> 00:10:48,960
of our own.

280
00:10:56,519 --> 00:10:57,159
I'm sorry.

281
00:11:01,559 --> 00:11:02,080
Jiaobao,

282
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:04,399
the market is changing so fast right now.

283
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:05,759
I'm under enormous pressure.

284
00:11:07,399 --> 00:11:08,480
You should get discharged soon too.

285
00:11:08,879 --> 00:11:10,240
There are people coming and going here.

286
00:11:10,360 --> 00:11:12,120
If someone films you having an episode,

287
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:13,879
it'll do more harm than good.

288
00:11:17,919 --> 00:11:19,200
You haven't had one lately, have you?

289
00:11:22,159 --> 00:11:22,480
No.

290
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:24,200
You still have to be careful.

